Package: dsVertClient
Type: Package
Title: DataSHIELD Client Functions for Vertically Partitioned Data
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("David", "Sarrat González", email = "david.sarrat@isglobal.org",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Miron", "Banjac", email = "miron.banjac@isglobal.org",
           role = "aut"),
    person("Juan R", "González", email = "juanr.gonzalez@isglobal.org",
           role = "aut")
  )
Description: Client-side DataSHIELD functions for privacy-preserving analysis
    of vertically partitioned federated data. Provides ECDH-PSI record
    alignment, GLM (Gaussian, Binomial, Poisson) with standard errors and
    p-values, Pearson correlation, and PCA. All protocols use Ring63 Beaver
    MPC with DCF wide spline link functions. No homomorphic encryption.
    Zero observation-level disclosure. Works with the companion dsVert
    server package.
